So you can see here the Central Powers count for the largest presence of European born in the US. And it’s even more stark than it appears, in terms of likely support for the Allies among immigrants; the large number of Russian immigrants is mainly Jews who are fleeing from the Tsar’s regime. So they’re not likely to support the policies of the Tsar’s government. Likewise, although Ireland is at this point part of the United Kingdom, they’re not especially keen on that fact, and so the Irish are not especially likely to support the policies of the British government. 
